# Now, apply Linear Interpolate for each layer of the raster
intp<-approxTime(r_0_ham, 6:18, rule = 2)

#Extract the month from the data.frame
tm<-intp[,1]

#Define a function for a linear model using lm
lm.func<-function(i) {lm(i ~ tm)}

#Define a r_0_ham data.frame without the month from intp
intp.r_0_ham<-intp[,-1]

#Creates a list of the lm coefficients for each column of intp.r_0_ham
lm.list<-apply(intp.r_0_ham, MARGIN=2, FUN=lm.func)

#Create a data.frame of the final month of your extrapolation; keep the name of tm data.frame
r_0_ham.pred<-data.frame(tm = 18)

#Make predictions for the final month for each element of lm.list
pred.points<-lapply(lm.list, predict, r_0_ham.pred)

#unlist the predicted points
fintime<-matrix(unlist(pred.points))

#Add the final year to the fintime matrix and transpond it
fintime.r_0_ham<-t(rbind(18,fintime))

#Convert the intp data.frame into a matrix
intp.ma<-as.matrix(intp)

#Append fintime.r_0_ham to intp.ma
intp.wt<-as.data.frame(rbind(intp.ma,fintime.r_0_ham))

#Perform an linear interpolation with approxTime again
approxTime(intp.wt, 6:18, rule = 2)
